==English==
===Etymology===
Greek arthro-, [[joint]] + [[-itis]], [[inflammation]]

===Noun===
'''athritis''' (''plural'' '''arthritides''')

# {{pathology}} Inflammation of a joint or joints causing pain, swelling and stiffness, and due to various causes such as infection, trauma, degenerative changes or metabolic disorders.

